        <ul>
            <li>The Louisiana state is called as ‘Cesarean Capital of the USA’ for 47.3% cesarean deliveries in 2017.</li>
            <li>In 2015, cesarean deliveries went up by 10 times in Latin American and Caribbean region in comparison to Central and West Africa.</li>
            <li>Data says the cesarean cases increased in the USA from 23% in 2000 to 32% in 2015. In the same period, the cesarean deliveries in the United Kingdom increased by 19.7% to 26.2% of births.</li>
            <li>According to an RTI information provided by the Government of NCT Delhi, the private hospitals in Delhi conducted 65 to 73% caesarean deliveries in 2014-15.</li>
